      "docs": "Domain-layer error returned by CatalogueToExtendedCratePort::encode. Carried for edge exposure: infrastructure defines impl From<CatalogueToExtendedCrateCodecError> for NewTypeGraphCodecError (a cross-crate impl). The B-side orphan impl insertion (phase1/builder.rs) already inserts this cross-crate impl into s_impls without checking for_type externality. The C-side build_impl_identity_map had a for_is_external filter that excluded cross-crate impls from c_impls, causing a false-positive Red (SMinusC_Reference). D3 (IN-13) removes the C-side filter so cross-crate impls appear symmetrically in both s_impls and c_impls (T012 done). Not modified in this track.",
